@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{telega-extras.el} extends the @samp{telega} package, an Emacs client for the Telegram messaging service. While @samp{telega} provides a comprehensive Telegram interface, this package adds convenience commands and integrations that streamline daily messaging workflows:

@itemize
@item
An intelligent buffer-switching command that cycles through chat, root, and archive buffers (@ref{Switching to telega}).
@item
Context-sensitive actions on URLs, buttons, and message input (@ref{Smart enter}).
@item
Capturing Telegram messages into Org mode (@ref{Org capture integration}).
@item
Sending files from Dired as Telegram attachments with automatic type detection (@ref{Sending files from Dired}).
@item
Audio message transcription with optional automatic sharing (@ref{Audio transcription}).
@item
Quick access to predefined chats and topics via a transient menu (@ref{Chat and topic navigation}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{paths} and @samp{telega}.

