@node Auto-sharing audio transcripts
@section Auto-sharing audio transcripts

@vindex telega-extras-auto-share-audio-transcript
The user option @code{telega-extras-auto-share-audio-transcript} controls whether the transcript of a voice note is automatically posted as a reply after transcription. When set to non-@code{nil}, and when the transcribed message was sent by you, the transcript is shared as a reply once it becomes available. The default value is @code{nil}, meaning transcripts are obtained but not automatically shared.

This option only takes effect when using @code{telega-extras-transcribe-audio} (@ref{Audio transcription}).

@node Chat configuration
@section Chat configuration

@vindex telega-extras-chats
The user option @code{telega-extras-chats} stores a plist describing Telegram chats and their topics. Each chat entry includes a name (string), an ID (integer), and optionally a nested plist of topics with their own names and IDs. This data is used by @code{telega-extras-open-chat} and the transient menu (@ref{Chat and topic navigation}) to navigate directly to specific chats or topic threads.

The default value is @code{nil}. You should populate this option with the chats you access most frequently. The chat and topic IDs can be obtained from the Telegram API or from @samp{telega} itself.

