@node Tab-bar integration
@section Tab-bar integration

@findex telega-extras-reset-tab-bar
The function @code{telega-extras-reset-tab-bar} schedules a tab-bar reset (via @code{tab-bar-extras-quick-reset} from @samp{tab-bar-extras.el}) one second after it is called. This is intended to be run after @samp{telega} loads, because @samp{telega} may add elements to the tab bar that require a refresh to display correctly.

@node Chat and topic lookup
@section Chat and topic lookup

@findex telega-extras-open-chat
@findex telega-extras-get-id
@findex telega-extras-get-last-topic-message
The function @code{telega-extras-open-chat} opens a chat by name and optionally navigates to a topic within it. It looks up the chat and topic IDs from @code{telega-extras-chats} using @code{telega-extras-get-id}, then either opens the topic thread (via @code{telega-msg-open-thread-or-topic}) or the chat directly (via @code{telega-chat-with}).

The function @code{telega-extras-get-id} translates chat and topic names into their numerical IDs by querying the @code{telega-extras-chats} plist. The function @code{telega-extras-get-last-topic-message} retrieves the last message in a given topic thread, which is needed to open the thread view.

@node Audio transcript helpers
@section Audio transcript helpers

@findex telega-extras-get-audio-transcript
@findex telega-extras-post-audio-transcript
The function @code{telega-extras-get-audio-transcript} extracts the transcript text from a voice note message if speech recognition has completed. The function @code{telega-extras-post-audio-transcript} formats a transcript and sends it as a reply to the original message. These functions support the transcription workflow described in @ref{Audio transcription}.

